## 3. Architectural objectives

The architecture must satisfy the following objectives:

### 3.1 Business objectives
- Support a public-facing digital catalogue of structured resources and services
- Enable tiered membership access with clear differentiation across Basic, Standard, and Premium
- Provide protected delivery of digital assets and member actions
- Support service operations such as discovery calls, customisation requests, implementation support, and strategic checkups
- Enable admin-led publishing, operational control, user oversight, and promotion management
- Provide a scalable foundation for future partner offers, recommendations, advanced analytics, and operational automation

### 3.2 Technical objectives
- Maintain a fast and coherent web application architecture
- Centralize security and access logic in server-validated layers
- Preserve a single deployable codebase while enforcing domain boundaries internally
- Reuse common content and discovery models across multiple user journeys
- Support staged operational hardening for launch and post-launch maturity
- Minimize unnecessary distributed-system complexity at the current stage

### 3.3 Delivery objectives
- Keep the architecture understandable to a small-to-medium engineering team
- Reduce duplication between public, member, and admin features
- Allow phased enhancement without large-scale rewrites
- Provide clear ownership boundaries for future platform governance

