### Platform Ops
Owns telemetry, notifications, admin role structures, and readiness checks

### Auth/System
Owns identity linkage, auth session interpretation, and provider integration points

## 19.4 Firestore design principles
- use explicit collection names with domain meaning
- preserve separation between operational queues when it adds clarity
- keep timestamps normalized and present on mutable records
- use status fields consistently for lifecycle management
- document index requirements for query-heavy admin and reporting views

