## 28. Scalability and growth architecture

## 28.1 Current scalability posture

The current architecture is suitable for early-to-mid scale usage where:
- application traffic is moderate
- content volume is manageable
- billing events are not massive in volume
- operational workflows are handled by a bounded admin team

## 28.2 Likely future scaling pressures
- larger search/discovery corpus
- more member workflow volume
- more admin reporting demands
- increased analytics event volume
- broader partner and offer complexity

## 28.3 Planned scale path

### Near-term
- keep modular monolith
- add stronger indexing and query governance
- add background job processing for retries and deferred work

### Mid-term
- introduce asynchronous processing for heavy side effects
- consider read-model projections for reporting-heavy views
- introduce search pre-indexing if discovery volume grows substantially

### Long-term
Only consider service extraction when a domain shows:
- materially different scaling needs
- independent release cadence
- stable interfaces
- unacceptable contention inside the monolith

