## 29. Background processing and async architecture

## 29.1 Current state

The platform is mostly synchronous, with some event-triggered patterns driven by webhooks and side effects.

## 29.2 Why async support is needed

Some operations should not remain inline forever:
- email retries
- notification fan-out
- promotion expiry processing
- analytics rollups
- search pre-indexing
- long-running report generation

## 29.3 Recommended target

Introduce a lightweight background job mechanism or scheduled task framework while keeping domain ownership in existing service modules.

## 29.4 Architectural rule

Async processing should be used for resilience and throughput, not to hide broken synchronous domain design.

