## 33. Final architecture position

New Platform Build should be treated as a **platform business system**, not merely a document portal.

It already contains the foundations of:
- managed content publishing
- public discovery
- membership and billing control
- protected asset delivery
- member operations
- admin operations
- promotions and temporary grants
- launch-readiness governance

The correct architectural framing is therefore:

> A modular monolith platform built with Next.js, Firebase, Firestore, and Square, organized around shared content, discovery, entitlement, billing lifecycle, service workflow, and admin operations domains, with strong server-side access control and a unified public/member/admin experience model.

The immediate architectural priority is not service decomposition. It is **operational hardening, deployment clarity, domain formalization, and governance discipline**.

That is how this project gets executed effectively rather than merely described impressively.

